- "Average fare" is the mean fare paid by passengers on the ship;
- "Ships with more than 500 passengers" are those with a total passenger count exceeding 500.

- "First class" refers to the highest class of travel on the ship;
- "Survival status" is represented by a binary value (0 = did not survive, 1 = survived);
- "Document count" indicates the number of documents each passenger has;
- "Survival statistics" include the total number of passengers, the number of survivors, and the survival rate for each class and sex combination.

